title: Merges use keys. Sometimes more than one.
pid: f3bfbd07-8bd2-4a0f-a219-591f201a6199
body: |2-
  Keys are what you match on.
  Maybe you just find the same person in both data sets (just one ID column).
  Maybe you have to compare person and year together (two ID columns).
  This depends on the unit of the data set.
